09:55.620 --> 10:05.880
the thrust of the Covenant books as a whole, it's certainly true that the land
is where the main battles are being fought and other stuff feeds into that but

10:05.880 --> 10:17.460
is not central. Hey, Covenant, at least in my experience with fantasy, I imagine
for a lot of readers too, Covenant is sort of an anti-hero. You know, being a

10:17.460 --> 10:26.940
leper for one reason, but also being a, doesn't want to be a hero in the first
place. Why pick somebody that was not in the traditional? Well, for one thing,

10:27.140 --> 10:35.780
you know, I mean, I wasn't aware of the tradition. I had read Lord of the Rings,
but other than that I hadn't read much fantasy myself. So I wasn't making a

10:35.780 --> 10:45.980
conscious decision to go for or against anything normal. I was just trying to
deal with something that seemed to me to be exciting and appropriate. Now, for

10:45.980 --> 10:57.840
me, the story started with the climax of the power that preserves. I have an
unbeliever confronting the evil principle and rising above it. Well, I had that

10:57.840 --> 11:06.000
idea in my head for like three years before I ever had, before I could figure
out who those guys were and how they got into that mess. That original idea,

11:06.120 --> 11:14.980
although it was very powerful to me, was also static. There was no story
attached. I got a story when it occurred to me that the person who was going to

11:14.980 --> 11:26.700
go from the real world to the fantasy world and reject the fantasy world in
favor of the real world should be somebody whose real world is unbearable and

11:26.700 --> 11:37.200
whose fantasy world is terrific. I mean, look at it the other way around.
Suppose you have a terrific real life. And you have these rotten fantasies. if

11:37.200 --> 11:46.380
you then say I don't care about the fantasy I'm going to stick with reality what
does that mean you know I mean you just that's normal self-interest anybody

11:46.380 --> 11:55.180
anybody who has a terrible time in their nightmares and a wonderful time in the
rest of their life is going to prefer the rest of their life it only becomes a

11:55.180 --> 12:06.420
moral statement when you have somebody who really hates their life because their
life is terrible and their dreams are just wonderful and they still say, I'm

12:06.420 --> 12:16.060
going to reject the dream because I know the difference and even though reality
is terrible, I'm going to still affirm reality. Now that, you know, may seem a

12:16.060 --> 12:23.340
little unbalanced or crazy to some people, but it is a moral statement of some
kind because there's no self-interest in it. It's not something that you do to

12:23.340 --> 12:33.240
make yourself feel better. It's something that you do as an ideal or as a
belief, a religious belief. And, of course, whose real life could be lousier

12:33.240 --> 12:42.360
than a leper's. Now, as soon as I thought of that, then I had a story. I had a
fantasy world, because all I had to do was invent a fantasy world that is the

12:42.360 --> 12:52.100
direct opposite of being a leper. And I had, you know, everything fell into
place for me as soon as I thought of that kind of thing. Now, I never intended

12:52.100 --> 13:00.620
that as an anti-hero kind of situation. From my point of view, the only thing
that makes Covenant an antihero is that he doesn't want to be a hero. He's

13:00.620 --> 13:09.340
afraid of being a hero. But he is a hero. From my point of view. And I think
most of my readers eventually get sucked into the point, even though they don't

13:09.340 --> 13:17.280
like him in the beginning. First they start to admit that he's got some reasons
for what he does and then they start grudgingly to respect what he's doing. And

13:17.280 --> 13:26.780
before you know it, people end up liking him and identifying with him as if he
were a normal hero. and that's certainly the way it is for me I cared a lot

13:26.780 --> 13:37.160
about this character from the very beginning and I never worked with him as
something that I would call anti-anything I knew he was having a tough time I

13:37.160 --> 13:46.400
knew it was rotten to be in the position that he was in and I knew from various
kinds of studies and research what sorts of psychological problems people who

13:46.400 --> 13:55.160
suffer from leprosy develop what does it feel like to be despised by everybody
around you for something that has nothing to do with what you did or didn't do.

13:55.460 --> 14:04.700
You just got this disease, you don't know why, everybody hates you. That exerts
a tremendous psychological stress and it doesn't make people beautiful. You

14:04.700 --> 14:15.840
don't become a nice guy just because you got leprosy. The pressure brings, any
kind of pressure, brings out the flaws in human nature. That's where you find

14:15.840 --> 14:21.720
out that there are areas where you're weak and there are areas where you're not
very graceful is when somebody puts a lot of pressure on you and you start to

14:21.720 --> 14:29.720
get a little nasty and you start to get a little impatient and you start to do
this and start to do that. It seemed obvious to me, particularly at the

14:29.720 --> 14:36.960
beginning, that Covenant is under tremendous kinds of psychological and emotional
pressure and he's not going to be a very likable guy. But what's going to

14:36.960 --> 14:45.340
happen, and of course I knew this all along, what's going to happen is that in
the course of coping with this dilemma, he was going to essentially reintegrate

14:45.340 --> 14:55.200
his whole personality and become a constructive individual who does know what he
cares about and who does love other people and who is willing to fight for that.

14:56.440 --> 15:04.880
So from my point of view, there was never any identification problem. I
identified with him a lot from the beginning. For a reader, it's different. A

15:04.880 --> 15:13.400
reader doesn't know where I'm going. And so they have to kind of evaluate things
as it goes along. And for many readers, in the beginning, covenant is just very

15:13.400 --> 15:24.940
obnoxious. then later they learn to kind of understand him a bit. I guess to me,
one of the paradoxes I guess it's a paradox that all six volumes is based upon

15:24.940 --> 15:34.340
is the idea that Covenant's power, his ability to combat despite Lord Foul, is
simply the fact that he is a leper and does have such a I guess a lousy life in

15:34.340 --> 15:38.480
the real world. That gives him a strength. Yeah, it gives him an emotional
strength.

15:41.420 --> 15:53.980
what passes for magic in the Covenant books really is just an external
expression of personality. The strength for magic always comes from inside the

15:53.980 --> 16:06.140
individual in this kind of world. And what creates emotional strength is what
makes magic. like Lord Morum, who it becomes in the first Chronicles becomes the

16:06.140 --> 16:15.180
strongest of the lords, really, and does something that nobody else has been
able to do in the end when he when he kills the giant raver that's attacking

16:15.180 --> 16:24.200
them. You know, what's really an issue for there is emotional strength. It's not
it's not that you that you know more than somebody else does you know more

16:24.200 --> 16:33.020
spells than somebody else does or you've studied a different book of Arcana and
have learned different kinds of magic or anything else. In this kind of world,

16:33.160 --> 16:40.860
magic doesn't hinge on that sort of thing. It hinges on the strengths and
weaknesses of your own personality. And that's where the danger comes from of

16:40.860 --> 16:51.980
course because people who have that susceptibility to pressure to where like
Kevin, they crack when things get too bad. Then they fall into despair and you

16:51.980 --> 17:03.960
get the same people who perform the ritual of desecration. The key issue is the
personality of the person who has the power. or their personality structure, how

17:03.960 --> 17:18.360
strong or how weak they are. And what Covenant becomes over the course of these
six books is this incredibly strong personality. And eventually, he becomes such

17:18.360 --> 17:28.900
a strong personality that in certain ways he doesn't need magic anymore. You'll
find this when you've read through to the end of White Gold Wilder, That he

17:28.900 --> 17:47.080
dominates situations without using magic anymore because he has become such a
