22:18.680 --> 22:28.420
relation to man, and what law can mean. And, of course, particularly in the
first trilogy, law is a very important concept for the lords. They mean

22:28.420 --> 22:39.560
something different than a set of rules. But in a way, it is a set of rules. For
them, law is the way nature works, and you have to live your life in service to

22:39.560 --> 22:50.260
the way nature works and in harmony with the way nature works. And if you become
a corruptive or destructive influence, then you're going against law. So, I

22:50.260 --> 22:59.280
mean, the thematic implications run in all kinds of directions. The same thing
is true, of course, for the name Thomas. Thomas was the disciple of Christ who

22:59.280 --> 23:09.580
doubted Christ's resurrection, who doubted the fundamental religious idea on
which 2,000 years Christian history was going to be built." Well, Covenant,

23:10.000 --> 23:23.260
Thomas Covenant, my character, is a doubter of a certain kind of sin. He takes
the really key point and rejects it for a while. And that allows me to imply

23:23.260 --> 23:35.260
various sorts of religious implications, which I like working with. Throughout
